//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_sa_forfeit}

NOTE: This operation forfeits a service account from the
{rbtgi_depot_project}.
It is a multi-role operation that can be invoked by any authenticated role with IAM admin access.

//axhopa_arg_parameter
{rbgt_service_account}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_SA_EMAIL»` provided as first argument
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if missing: "Service account email required"

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate*:
.. {rbbc_require}
caller has valid OAuth token with `https://www.googleapis.com/auth/cloud-platform` scope
.. {rbbc_store}
`«ACCESS_TOKEN»` from caller context

//axhos_step
. *Forfeit Service Account*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/delete[iam.projects.serviceAccounts.delete] with:
... method: `DELETE`
... endpoint: `https://iam.googleapis.com/v1/projects/{rbrr_depot_project_id}/serviceAccounts/«INPUT_SA_EMAIL»`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «ACCESS_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response OR HTTP 404 (already forfeit)
.. {rbbc_warn}
if HTTP 404: "Service account not found (already forfeit)"

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtgi_depot_project}
. *Display Results*:
.. {rbbc_show}
forfeit operation completed

//axhoc_completion
Successful completion is indicated by the "forfeit operation completed" message.

